    "id": "slide6",
    "eyebrow": "Settler Perspectives",
    "num": "06",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settler Perspectives</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Why Did Anglo Settlers Push for Independence?</h2><ul><li>Desire for political representation and local control</li><li>Opposition to Mexican laws restricting immigration and slavery</li><li>Cultural affinity with the United States and its democratic ideals</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Anglo settlers sought greater autonomy and political rights, opposing Mexican centralist policies. Their cultural and economic ties to the U.S. influenced their push for independence, viewing Mexican rule as restrictive and foreign. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s14\">[14]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Consider settlers’ reactions to Mexican attempts to enforce immigration restrictions and anti-slavery laws.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify key motivations behind Anglo settlers’ support for revolution.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not assume all settlers had identical motivations; some were more pragmatic, others ideological.</p></div></div>",
