    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Mexican Government Perspective</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Why Did Mexico Resist Texan Independence?</h2><ul><li>Sought to maintain territorial integrity and national sovereignty</li><li>Feared loss of valuable land and resources</li><li>Concerned about U.S. expansionism and settler disloyalty</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Mexico viewed Texas as a vital northern territory and resisted settler demands that threatened its control. The government was wary of U.S. intentions and settler loyalty, leading to stricter enforcement of laws and military responses. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Analyze Mexican government decrees aimed at limiting Anglo immigration and enforcing laws.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain Mexico’s reasons for opposing Texas independence from its own perspective.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid portraying Mexico as simply oppressive; consider its legitimate concerns about sovereignty.</p></div></div>",
