    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Summary Checkpoint</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Review: Texas’s Geography and Early Political Conditions</h2><ul><li>Texas was a borderland with diverse populations and contested borders</li><li>Mexican policies initially encouraged, then restricted Anglo immigration</li><li>Cultural and legal differences fueled tensions leading to unrest</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This checkpoint reviews key points about Texas’s geography, demographics, and political conditions under Mexican rule that set the stage for revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s14\">[14]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Recall how Mexican immigration laws changed over time and affected settlers.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Summarize in your own words why Texas was a region prone to conflict in the early 1800s.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid mixing up the timeline of Mexican policies and settler responses.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide8\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best describes the political status of Texas before the revolution?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;An independent republic&quot;,&quot;A Mexican territory with increasing Anglo-American settlers&quot;,&quot;A U.S. state&quot;,&quot;A British colony&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;Texas was a Mexican territory experiencing demographic changes due to Anglo-American immigration, which contributed to tensions leading to the revolution.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Describe the significance of Sam Houston&#39;s leadership during the Texas War of Independence.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should explain Houston&#39;s role in uniting Texian forces, his strategic leadership at key battles such as San Jacinto, and how his actions contributed to Texas gaining independence.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Sam Houston was the commander of Texian forces and led them to a decisive victory at the Battle of San Jacinto, which effectively ended the war and secured Texas independence.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Sam Houston united Texian forces and led them to victory at San Jacinto&quot;,&quot;He was a key military leader whose strategy won the war&quot;,&quot;Houston&#39;s leadership was crucial in securing Texas independence&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
