    "eyebrow": "Transition",
    "num": "09",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">09</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Transition</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">From Conditions to Causes: What Sparked the Revolution?</h2><ul><li>Political centralization by Mexican government angered settlers</li><li>Immigration restrictions limited Anglo-American growth</li><li>Cultural clashes over laws, language, and governance escalated</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Building on the context, this slide introduces the main causes of the Texas War of Independence, highlighting the clash between Mexican centralism and settler demands for autonomy. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s14\">[14]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Identify how Mexican centralist policies conflicted with settler expectations.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> List the main causes of the revolution based on political and cultural tensions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not reduce causes to a single issue; multiple overlapping factors contributed.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide9\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best describes the political status of Texas before the revolution?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;An independent republic&quot;,&quot;A Mexican territory with increasing Anglo-American settlers&quot;,&quot;A U.S. state&quot;,&quot;A British colony&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;Texas was a Mexican territory experiencing demographic changes due to Anglo-American immigration, which contributed to tensions leading to the revolution.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Describe the significance of Sam Houston&#39;s leadership during the Texas War of Independence.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should explain Houston&#39;s role in uniting Texian forces, his strategic leadership at key battles such as San Jacinto, and how his actions contributed to Texas gaining independence.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Sam Houston was the commander of Texian forces and led them to a decisive victory at the Battle of San Jacinto, which effectively ended the war and secured Texas independence.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Sam Houston united Texian forces and led them to victory at San Jacinto&quot;,&quot;He was a key military leader whose strategy won the war&quot;,&quot;Houston&#39;s leadership was crucial in securing Texas independence&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
