    "eyebrow": "Cause Analysis",
    "num": "11",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">11</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cause Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Immigration Restrictions and Settler Growth</h2><ul><li>Mexico limited Anglo immigration to control Texas population</li><li>Settlers viewed restrictions as threats to economic and political goals</li><li>Illegal immigration and smuggling increased tensions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Mexico’s attempts to restrict Anglo immigration aimed to maintain control but clashed with settlers’ desire for expansion, contributing to conflict escalation. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Review Mexican laws restricting immigration and settlers’ responses.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss how immigration policies can affect political stability in frontier regions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not overlook the role of illegal immigration in escalating tensions.</p></div></div>",
